_pdbx_molecule_features.prd_id    PRD_000117 
_pdbx_molecule_features.name      'ARYLOMYCIN A2' 
_pdbx_molecule_features.type      Lipopeptide 
_pdbx_molecule_features.class     Antibiotic 
_pdbx_molecule_features.details   
;ARYLOMYCIN A2 IS A BIARYL-BRIDGED LIPOPEPTIDE.
 THE SCAFFOLD IS MADE OF TWO PARTS:
 (1) N-TERM EXOCYCLIC TRIPEPTIDE
 (2) A TRICYCLIC PEPTIDE, WITH [3,3] BIARYL BOND
     BETWEEN RESIDUE 4 AND 6
 AN ISO-C12 FATTY ACID IS LINKED TO RESIDUE 1.
;
